<TITLE> Three 'dacoits' killed in 'gunfight' in Barguna </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barguna, Jun 11 (bdnews24.com) Three alleged 'dacoits' have been killed in a so-called 'gunfight' with the RAB and Coast Guard personnel in Barguna. The occurrence happened in the early hours of Friday on the Baleshwar riverside at Patharghata Upazila of Barguna, police officials said. The alleged criminals were identified as Arab Ali alias Company, Kuddus Molah alias Nati Kuddus and Idris alias Ranga Idris. Patharghata police chief Mahe Alam told bdnews24.com that on receiving information that the men were preparing for a robbery, a team of RAB-8 led by Lieutenant Mahiuddin and Coast Guard personnel took up positions at about 1.30 at night. Three were killed as a 'gunfight' erupted between the robbers and the law enforcers, Alam said. Police also recovered four home-made guns, five Light Machine Guns, an Air gun and more than 300 rounds of bullets from the spot. bdnews2
